[Civ. No. 3541. First Appellate District, Division One. November 3, 1920.] SAMUEL BRASK et al., Respondents, v. FRANK BAR-NET, as Sheriff, etc., et al., Appellants.

The facts are the same as those stated in the opinion in Brask v. Cox et al., ante, p. 721 [194 Pac. 292].

F. A. Berlin for Appellants.

J. E. Hood and Chas. E. Snook for Respondents.

THE COURT.

The facts in this case are identical with those in the case of Brask v. Cox et al., ante, p. 721, [194 Pac. 292], and which are fully set forth in said decision, wherein the judgment was affirmed. It follows that the judgment herein must be affirmed, and it is so ordered.
